ID   HTH_TCS_reg
DE   HTH domain in two-component system regulators
AU   Bateman A;0000-0002-6982-4660
SE   TED:A0LBC4_TED01
GA   27.00 27.00;
TC   29.30 28.50;
NC   26.80 25.80;
BM   hmmbuild  -o /dev/null HMM SEED
SM   hmmsearch --cpu 8 -Z 90746521 -E 1000 HMM pfamseq
TP   Domain
CC   This entry represents a helix-turn-helix (HTH) DNA-binding domain
CC   (approximately 112-150 residues, positions 8-150) found in
CC   two-component signal transduction system regulators. STRING analysis
CC   shows strong associations with histidine kinase (Pfam:PF00512),
CC   HATPase (Pfam:PF02518), response regulator (Pfam:PF00072), PAS
CC   domains (Pfam:PF08448, Pfam:PF13188), and HAMP (Pfam:PF00672),
CC   confirming its role in bacterial signal transduction. The family is
CC   found in Alphaproteobacteria, particularly in Rhodobacterales
CC   (Paracoccus, Paracoccaceae, Roseobacteraceae).
